Volume 7 Issue 01
January 07, 2003

**********************************************

Dear Education Professionals, 
Welcome to What's New This Week at Education World, published weekly as a free service by Education World(R). You are receiving this newsletter because you have signed up to receive updates of What's New at Education World. If you enjoy this newsletter, please feel free to forward it to other teachers. If this newsletter has been forwarded to you, you may sign up at http://www.educationworld.com/maillist.shtml.

**********************************************

Education World's newsletter is brought to you by TobaccoFreeKids.org

Please Help Protect Kids from Big Tobacco

Almost 90 percent of smokers start smoking at or before the age of 18 and kids spend almost a third of their waking time in school.   We need your help to stop this deadly cycle. Teachers and schools are in an important position to educate kids about the dangers of tobacco and prevent them from starting to smoke.  Some states have reduced middle school smoking rates by as much as 40%.  Our kids deserve the same access to these programs.  Click here,  http://www.educationworld.com/go/base?id=AEH to tell the Governor it is time to fund tobacco prevention programs in our schools and in our state.

