LESSON PLANNING
-------------------------------

Math Fun! (Volume 2)
http://www.educationworld.com/a_lesson/lesson293.shtml
Math class doesn’t have to be stay-in-your-seat quiet. Kids will love practicing their computation skills with these six activities -- in which the emphasis is on the “active.” In fact, they'll beg to do them again and again!  
Included: Activities that involve dice, playing cards, candy, and cameras!

Teacher-Submitted Lesson:  Positive and Negative Integers -- A Card Game
http://www.educationworld.com/a_tsl/archives/03-1/lesson001.shtml
A simple card game teaches addition and subtraction of positive and/or negative numbers.

Writing Bug: It’s Great to Be My Age
http://www.educationworld.com/a_lesson/writing_bug/writingbug021.shtml
Nine great reasons it’s great to be nine! (Or ten reasons it’s great to be ten, or…)

January Coloring Calendar
http://www.educationworld.com/a_lesson/calendar/jan03.shtml
Plus…
Twenty-Five Ideas for Using Education World's Monthly Coloring Calendars
http://www.educationworld.com/a_lesson/lesson272.shtml

Martin Luther King Day 2003
http://www.educationworld.com/holidays/archives/mlking_2000.shtml
January 20th is Martin Luther King Day. We have articles, lesson ideas, books, activities, and much more -- all to help you meet your holiday needs -- in this updated archive page!

Celebrate the 100th Day in 100 Ways
http://www.educationworld.com/a_lesson/lesson149.shtml
